This is the AmigaGuide® file kls.guide, produced by Makeinfo-1.55 from 
the input file kls.texi.

   This file describes the Best Screen Clearing Utility Ever Made, version
13.762 for the Commodore Amiga computers running AmigaOS 2.04 or higher.

   Copyright (C) 1990, 1991, 1992, 1993, 1994 Martin Mares, MJSoft System
Software.

   This documentation may be distributed in any form, including (but not
limited to) electronic and printed versions, but no user is allowed to print
more pages than the largest amount which fits in a sphere with diameter equal
to one light year.


@Node Main "kls.guide"
@Next "Preface"

Introduction
************

   The @{i}Kls@{ui} utility has been written to simplify one of the most frequent tasks
performed by almost any user -- clearing of the screen. This magical operation
can delete, scratch, zap and rewrite any information written on your screen.


 @{" Preface " Link "Preface"} 		How to read this documentation
