How to read this manual
***********************

   You may read this manual in any way you wish to do it in. If this is an
original English version, you might (but you needn't) try to read it from the
left to the right, from the top to the bottom. In case you have received a
Hebrew translation of the manual, this paragraph should give you some other
information, but it doesn't because this is not a Hebrew translation.

   Also reading of this manual in a hex-editor is possible, though it is not
recommended to be done by people which don't remember ASCII codes of all
characters, at least in both normal and reversed order.

   For more information about reading of this file, find the book "A practical
introduction to reading of books", written by James Reader.


@EndNode

