Distribution
************

   Yes, this program can be distributed. The simplest proof of this rule is the
fact that you have received this software package.

   This package can be freely distributed as long as the following conditions
are met:

   @{b}*@{ub} The total length of all the files in this archive is not decreased by more
     than 23 percent.

   @{b}*@{ub} The copyright notice of Atari corporation is not added to any file. (Any
     other copyright notices may be added, but they must not be larger than the
     copyright of the original author).

   @{b}*@{ub} No key files are distributed along with the software. (Each key file
     contains name of the user Kls has been registered to and is therefore very
     simple to identify.)

   @{b}*@{ub} Lines 21-23 of the documentation are not removed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Highly explosive or corrosive substances are not distributed in the same
     archive as this file is.

   @{b}*@{ub} The archive is not packed by @{b}LhA@{ub} version @{b}176.13@{ub} or higher.

   @{b}*@{ub} No more than 137 dollars (or an equivalent in any other currency) is
     charged per single distribution disk.

   This  software  is  provided  "AS  IS" without warranty of any kind, either
expressed  or implied.  The author is not responsible for any damage caused by
it.

   All rights reversed.

   Special permission is given to Fred Fish to include this software on his
@{i}Fish disks.@{ui} Another more special permission is given to all people with name
ending with the @{b}y@{ub} letter to freely delete all the files contained in this
archive.


@EndNode

