Options
*******

   This program has a lot of options which control various special features.
All of these options are displayed when you enter the @{b}?@{ub} character as a
parameter and their names are self-descriptive, therefore it has no use to
explain them here.

About undocumented options
==========================

   All the options are undocumented, because the author is too lazy to mention
them in the documentation.


@EndNode

@Node "Requirements" "kls.guide/Requirements"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Options"
@Toc "Main"

Requirements
************

   @{b}Kls@{ub} requires:

   @{b}*@{ub} Kickstart 2.04 or higher.

   @{b}*@{ub} The @{b}ss.library@{ub} written by the same author. (Included in this archive.)

   @{b}*@{ub} Some amount of free memory.

   @{b}*@{ub} Some amount of free time.

   @{b}*@{ub} Some amount of free electricity.

   @{b}*@{ub} No more than five ghosts floating above the disk drive.


@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "kls.guide/Installation"
@Next "Thanks"
@Prev "Requirements"
@Toc "Main"

Installation
************

   @{b}Kls@{ub} is very easy to install -- simply double-click on the @{b}Install KLS@{ub} icon
and the Installer will do everything for you.

   If you have some special requirements about the installation, install the
program manually.


@EndNode

